{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "targeted_sweep2_hashrate_economic",
    "description": "Map the 2D decision boundary between hashrate_split and economic_split \u2014 the two dominant parameters from the exploratory sweep (correlations +0.554 and +0.666 respectively). This produces the fundamental \"decision surface\" separating v26-dominant from v27-dominant outcomes across the core parameter space.\nFrom targeted_sweep1 (economic \u00d7 committed grid at hash=0.25):\n  - econ >= 0.82: v27 wins regardless of pool commitment\n  - econ <= 0.35: v26 wins regardless of pool commitment\n  - econ 0.50\u20130.70: pool commitment inversion around Foundry flip-point ~0.214\nThis sweep maps how those thresholds shift as hashrate_split varies.\npool_committed_split is fixed at 0.50 (above the Foundry flip-point at ~0.214) so the non-monotonic inversion from targeted_sweep1 does not contaminate the surface. All other parameters at medians from the exploratory sweep.\nGrid: 6 hashrate levels \u00d7 7 economic levels = 42 scenarios Duration: ~22h at 32 min/scenario\n",
    "spec_file": "specs/targeted_sweep2_hashrate_economic.yaml",
    "n_samples": 42,
    "n_parameters": 16,
